            "id": "1847420d704e4db286236",
            "questionText": "A spaceship travels past Earth at a constant speed of $!$0.8c$!$. An astronaut on the spaceship measures the length of the spaceship to be $!$L_0 = 100 \\; m$!$. What length would an observer on Earth measure for the spaceship, taking into account length contraction?",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "81d36a81ad00485fa5f08",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula that relates the proper length to the contracted length in the context of length contraction. Which of the following formulas applies?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a2cc780f-e223-46ae-8ac0-d8b76d0c5385",
                        "8f95aa1b-0eb7-42ba-bd59-8b8b8322f61a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$L = L_0 \\sqrt{1-\\frac{v^2}{c^2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$L = L_0 \\left(1-\\frac{v}{c}\\right)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$L = L_0 \\left(1-\\frac{v^2}{c^2}\\right)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "2b9be194ccf740c984e11",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you have the proper formula, let's compute the term $!$1-\\frac{v^2}{c^2}$!$ given that the spaceship's speed is $!$v = 0.8c$!$. What numerical value does this expression evaluate to?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.36"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a2cc780f-e223-46ae-8ac0-d8b76d0c5385"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "f82b75fd5cd941849e42b",
                    "stepText": "Now, use the value you just calculated to determine the contracted length. Multiply the proper length $!$L_0 = 100 \\; m$!$ by the square root of your computed value. What is the length measured by an observer on Earth?",
